[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mortal Kombat actor Darren Shahlavi has been found dead

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The actor who played Kano in the series Mortal Kombat: Legacy has died.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Darren Shahlavi was 42 years old.
His agent confirmed to Variety that he had died in his sleep and was found by his roommate.
Darren's younger sister Malouse wrote on Twitter: "Don't know how to express the emotions I'm feeling right now. Last night I found out my dearest brother had past (sic) away, he was a true inspiration to so many people including myself."
The actor began martial arts training in England as a child, before moving to Hong Kong and becoming a stunt man.
He moved to Hollywood after being cast as the villain in kung fu film Tai Chi Chuan.
As well as the Mortal Kombat series, Darren Shahlavi featured alongside Eddie Murphy in I-Spy and The Final Cut with Robin Williams.
More recently he had worked on DC Comics-inspired show Arrow.
